    "# Data model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "cell_style": "split"
   },
   "source": [
    "- pupil signal is made up of a slowly (<.1 Hz) fluctuating process\n",
    "- and stereotypic responses to (internal or external):\n",
    "    - Pupil-response function (PRF)\n",
    "- the amplitude of the events is variable over time\n",
    "- the shape of the PRF is fixed per subject or can vary over time"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "## Estimate tonic and phasic components\n",
    "\n",
    "- per-trial estimates of tonic/phasic pupillary responses\n",
    "\n",
    "*Traditionally:*\n",
    "    \n",
    "- tonic (baseline): mean signal in interval [-200,0] ms before stimulus\n",
    "- phasic (response): \n",
    "    - difference peak/max in interval [0,2000] ms post-stimulus to baseline\n",
    "    - difference mean in time-range of expected peak, e.g., [800,1200] ms post-stim to baseline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "hide_input": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "d2=dd.sub_slice(4500, 13000, units=\"ms\") # take a small part for visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "with io.capture_output() as cap:\n",
    "    tonic_est =d2.stat_per_event((-200,0), statfct=np.mean)\n",
    "    phasic_est=d2.stat_per_event((-0,2000), statfct=np.max)-tonic_est\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))\n",
    "d2.plot(model=False, units=\"ms\")\n",
    "plt.vlines(d2.event_onsets, *plt.ylim(), color=\"grey\", alpha=0.5)\n",
    "plt.plot(d2.event_onsets, tonic_est, \"o\",color=\"red\")\n",
    "plt.plot(d2.event_onsets, phasic_est+tonic_est, \"o\",color=\"blue\");\n",
    "plt.title(\"Traditional tonic/phasic estimates\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- traditional method can mistake build-up of responses for baseline fluctuations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "hide_input": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Novel Algorithm for baseline extraction\n",
    "\n",
    "- in the absence of events, the pupil goes back to baseline\n",
    "- therefore: throughs in the the curve are indicative of baseline \n",
    "\n",
    "**Algorithm:**\n",
    "- detect throughs\n",
    "- find the most \"prominent\" ones \n",
    "- create smooth curve through these points that stays below signal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "hide_input": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x360 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "d=pp.create_fake_pupildata(ntrials=50, isi=1500.0, rtdist=(800,100),  \n",
    "                           prop_spurious_events=0.02 )\\\n",
    "    .lowpass_filter(cutoff=2)\\\n",
    "    .scale()\\\n",
    "    .sub_slice(5,25,units=\"sec\")\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10,5)); d.plot(interactive=False, model=False, units=\"sec\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- lowest throughs are prioritized\n",
    "- account for build-up of responses that look like baseline fluctuations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Extract peaks/throughs and rate their prominence"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "hide_input": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "-"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1080x360 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "peaks_ix=signal.find_peaks(-d.sy)[0]\n",
    "prominences=signal.peak_prominences(-d.sy, peaks_ix)[0]\n",
    "peaks=d.tx[peaks_ix]\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(15,5)); \n",
    "d.plot(model=False, units=\"sec\")\n",
    "plt.errorbar(peaks/1000., d.sy[peaks_ix], np.vstack((np.zeros_like(prominences), prominences)), 0, \"o\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topographic_prominence>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "hide_input": true,
    "slideshow": {

   },
   "source": [
    "## Smooth curve through peaks...\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "cell_style": "center"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x432 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "interp_methods=[\"nearest\",\"linear\",\"quadratic\",\"cubic\"]\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))\n",
    "for i,met in enumerate(interp_methods):\n",
    "    plt.subplot(2,2,i+1)\n",
    "    f=scipy.interpolate.interp1d(peaks, d.sy[peaks_ix], kind=met, fill_value=\"extrapolate\")\n",
    "    d.plot(baseline=False, model=False, units=\"ms\")\n",
    "    plt.plot(d.tx, f(d.tx))\n",
    "    plt.gca().axes.get_xaxis().set_visible(False)\n",
    "    plt.ylim(d.sim_baseline.min(), d.sy.max())\n",
    "    plt.title(met)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- simple interpolate between lower peaks?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Better Solution: B-Spline basis functions\n",
    "- weighted sum of B-spline basis functions (knots peaks): guarantees smoothness \n",
    "- customized fit to go through peaks and stay below signal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "hide_input": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "-"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1440x576 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "knots=np.concatenate( ([d.tx.min()], peaks, [d.tx.max()]) ) ## peaks as knots\n",
    "B=pp.bspline(d.tx, knots, 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(20,8))\n",
    "plt.subplot(2,1,1)\n",
    "plt.plot(d.tx, B);\n",
    "plt.plot(peaks, 0.8+np.zeros_like(peaks), \".\");\n",
    "plt.subplot(2,1,2)\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(10):\n",
    "    coef=np.random.randn(B.shape[1])\n",
    "    sig=np.dot(B,coef)\n",
    "    plt.plot(d.tx, sig, color=\"grey\", alpha=0.2)\n",
    "plt.plot(peaks, d.sy[peaks_ix], \"o\", color=\"red\")    \n",
    "d.plot(simulated=False, units=\"ms\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Staying \"below the signal\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "hide_input": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "-"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1440x360 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ny=800\n",
    "x=d.tx\n",
    "pad=0.5\n",
    "y=np.linspace(d.sy.min()-pad, d.sy.max()+pad, ny)\n",
    "[X,Y]=np.meshgrid(x,y)\n",
    "\n",
    "SY=np.tile(d.sy, (ny,1))\n",
    "py=pp.p_asym_laplac_kappa(-1*(Y-SY), 0, 1, 0.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "def prominence_to_lambda(w, lam_min=1, lam_max=100):\n",
    "        w2=lam_min+((w-np.min(w))/(np.max(w-np.min(w))))*(lam_max-lam_min)\n",
    "        return w2\n",
    "    \n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(20,5))\n",
    "d2=d.copy()\n",
    "start=d.tx[0]\n",
    "d2.tx=d.tx-start\n",
    "plt.imshow(py, origin='lower', cmap=\"jet\", aspect=\"auto\", alpha=0.2, extent=[0,d2.tx.max(),d2.sy.min()-pad, d2.sy.max()+pad])\n",
    "plt.plot(d2.tx, d2.sy, color=\"green\")\n",
    "plt.errorbar(peaks-start, d2.sy[peaks_ix], yerr=prominence_to_lambda(prominences)/200., fmt=\"o\", color=\"black\", elinewidth=5);\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "- estimate coefficients B-spline\n",
    "- criteria:\n",
    "    1. the curve has to be (almost) completely below the pupil-signal\n",
    "    2. it should go through the high-prominence peaks with high probability\n",
    "    3. it should go through the lower-prominence peaks with lower probability\n",
    "- use: Asymmetric Laplace distribution\n",
    "- parameters: \n",
    "    - $\\mu$ (peak location)\n",
    "    - $\\lambda$ (inverse variance, \"wideness\") \n",
    "    - $\\kappa$ (assymetry parameter)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "- distribution centered at signal $\\rightarrow$ $\\mu=0$\n",
    "- set asymmetry parameter $\\kappa$ as follows:\n",
    "    1. specify the probability $p_a$ that the baseline-curve can take on values above the pupil signal, e.g., $p_a=0.05$\n",
    "    2. using the properties of the distribution determine $$\\kappa=\\frac{\\sqrt{p_a}}{\\sqrt{1-p_a}}$$\n",
    "- no matter what $\\lambda$ is chosen, the negative part of the distribution will integrate to $p_a$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "kappa= 0.22941573387056177\n",
      "Proportion negative= 0.052898137321281825\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x360 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mu=0\n",
    "lam=5\n",
    "pa=0.05\n",
    "kappa=np.sqrt(pa)/np.sqrt(1-pa)\n",
    "print(\"kappa=\",kappa)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n",
    "y=np.linspace(-1,10,500)\n",
    "py=pp.p_asym_laplac_kappa(y,0,5,kappa)\n",
    "plt.plot(y,py)\n",
    "propneg=np.sum(py[y<=0])/np.sum(py)\n",
    "print(\"Proportion negative=\",propneg)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "hide_input": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### prominence of the peaks\n",
    "\n",
    "- map the prominence of the peaks to the width of this distribution: \n",
    "    - mapping prominence $\\rightarrow$ $\\lambda$\n",
    "- how far below the signal can the baseline go? parameter: $\\lambda_{sig}$\n",
    "- assume z-transformed PD, so 1 unit is pretty large: $\\lambda_{sig}=1$\n",
    "- for the highest-prominence peaks, the baseline-curve \"snuggles\" tightly against the signal\n",
    "- $\\lambda_{max}=100$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1080x360 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(15,5))\n",
    "lam_sig=1.0\n",
    "lam_max=100.0\n",
    "y=np.linspace(-1,10,500)\n",
    "py1=pp.p_asym_laplac_kappa(y,0,lam_sig,kappa)\n",
    "py2=pp.p_asym_laplac_kappa(y,0,lam_max,kappa)\n",
    "plt.subplot(121); plt.plot(y,py1); plt.title(r\"$\\lambda_{sig}=$%s\"%lam_sig);\n",
    "plt.subplot(122); plt.plot(y,py2); plt.title(r\"$\\lambda_{max}=$%s\"%lam_max);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "- the signal should be closer to the lower peaks than to the rest of the signal but can still go away if the prominence is very low\n",
    "- we therefore set the lower boundary for $\\lambda$ for any peak to be the same as for the rest of the signal $\\lambda_{min}=\\lambda_{sig}$\n",
    "- define mapping \n",
    "$$\\text{prominence}\\rightarrow \\lambda$$\n",
    "- such that $\\lambda \\in [\\lambda_{min},\\lambda_{max}]$ and higher prominence is associated with higher $\\lambda$\n",
    "- we start by mapping the (strictly positive) prominence $\\rho_i$ into the interval [0,1] and then map it linearly into $[\\lambda_{min},\\lambda_{max}]$\n",
    "$$\\lambda_i=\\lambda_{min}+\\frac{\\rho_i-\\min_i\\rho_i}{\\max_i(\\rho_i-\\min_i\\rho_i)}\\left(\\lambda_{max}-\\lambda_{min}\\right) $$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1440x360 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# convert\n",
    "w=prominence_to_lambda(prominences)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(20,5))\n",
    "plt.subplot(121)\n",
    "plt.hist(w);\n",
    "plt.title(r\"Distribution of the $\\lambda$ values\");\n",
    "plt.subplot(122)\n",
    "y=np.linspace(-0.5,2,500)\n",
    "for i,cw in enumerate(w):\n",
    "    py=pp.p_asym_laplac_kappa(y, 0, cw, kappa)\n",
    "    plt.plot(y,py, color=\"grey\", alpha=0.5)\n",
    "plt.title(r\"Distributions for these $\\lambda$ values\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Estimate baseline\n",
    "\n",
    "- implemented as Bayesian model (Stan)\n",
    "- free parameters are the spline-coefficients"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "WARNING:pystan:Automatic Differentiation Variational Inference (ADVI) is an EXPERIMENTAL ALGORITHM.\n",

   },
   "source": [
    "- baseline seems to \"high\"\n",
    "- because of accumulation of pupil-responses to stimuli\n",
    "- **solution:** \n",
    "    1. estimate responses riding on top of signal \n",
    "    2. remove them\n",
    "    3. repeat baseline estimation"
   ]
  },

     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Summary Algorithm baseline-extraction\n",
    "\n",
    "1. find throughs in signal\n",
    "2. rate them by prominence\n",
    "3. create B-spline basis-functions at location of throughs\n",
    "4. estimate B-coefficients using Bayesian model $\\rightarrow$ first estimate for baseline\n",
    "5. subtract baseline from signal\n",
    "6. estimate response-model using default PRF and subtract from data\n",
    "7. repeat steps 1. - 4. to get final baseline estimate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Pupil-response function (PRF)\n",
    "\n",
    "- Hoeks + Levelt, 1993 measured resonse to attentional stimulus\n",
    "\n",
    "![huhu](../data/stuff/hoeks_levelt_fig.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "- model: $$h(t)=t^{n}e^{-nt/t_{max}}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### pupil-response function model: $h(t)=t^{n}e^{-nt/t_{max}}$\n",
    "\n",
    "- parameters: location ($t_{max}$) and spread ($n$)"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "## data extract from original paper and saved in a CSV file\n",
    "hl_data=pd.read_csv(\"../data/stuff/tabula-Hoeks-Levelt1993_Article_PupillaryDilationAsAMeasureOfA.csv\", sep=\";\")\n",
    "hl_data[\"tmax\"]=hl_data[\"tmax\"]*1000. ## our implementation uses ms, HL use seconds\n",
    "## between-subject variability\n",
    "hl_per_subj=hl_data.groupby(\"subj\").aggregate([np.mean,np.std])[[\"n\",\"tmax\"]]\n",
    "hl_between=hl_per_subj.aggregate([np.mean,np.std]).filter(like=\"mean\", axis=0)\n",
    "hl_between"
   ]
  },

    "d6=pp.create_fake_pupildata(ntrials=100, isi=750.0, rtdist=(300,100), prop_spurious_events=0)\\\n",
    "    .downsample(fsd=20).scale()\n",
    "\n",
    "real_baseline=pp.stat_event_interval(d6.tx, d6.sim_baseline, d6.event_onsets, [0,0])\n",
    "real_response=d6.sim_response_coef\n",
    "naive_baseline=d6.stat_per_event([-200,0])\n",
    "naive_response=d6.stat_per_event([800,1200])-naive_baseline\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"BL      : Correlation(real, traditional) = %.2f\"%pearsonr(real_baseline, naive_baseline)[0])\n",

    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Validation of the method\n",
    "\n",
    "- dependence of tonic/phasic recovery as a function of the tuning parameters of the algorithm\n",
    "- robustness of method\n",
    "    - against noise-level\n",
    "    - against mis-specification (PRF pars)\n",
    "    - against unknown \"events\"\n",
    "- performance for different designs (ISI/RT)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Outcome variable**: Correlation with \"true\" baseline/response coefficients"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "hideCode": false,
    "hidePrompt": false,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "### setting tuning parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "- scanning the tuning parameters for the B-Spline based baseline estimation\n",
    "- `lam_sig` (float) - parameter steering how much the baseline is shaped by the non-peaks of the signal\n",
    "- `lam_min`,`lam_max` (float) ‚Äì parameters mapping how much low- and high-prominence peaks influence the baseline\n",
    "- `niter` (1 or 2) - use 1 or two iterations of the procedure"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 63,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x300 with 7 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "nbname=\"tonic_phasic_validation\"\n",
    "path=\"stuff/results/\"\n",
    "sim_label=\"tonic_phasic5\"\n",
    "fname=os.path.join(path,\"{nb}_{sim}.ft\".format(nb=nbname,sim=sim_label))\n",
    "res=pd.read_feather(fname)\n",
    "colnames=np.array(res.columns)[:-2]\n",
    "df=pd.melt(res, id_vars=colnames, value_vars=[\"est_bl\",\"naive_bl\"])\n",
    "df[\"estimate\"]=[\"new\" if \"est\" in v else \"naive\" for v in df.variable]\n",
    "df[\"method\"]=df[['estimate', 'niter']].astype(str).apply('-'.join, axis=1)\n",
    "(gg.ggplot(df, gg.aes(x=\"lam_sig\", y=\"value\",color=\"method\"))+\n",
    "     gg.stat_summary(fun_y=np.median, \n",
    "                     fun_ymin=lambda y: np.mean(y)-np.std(y),#np.quantile(y,0.05),\n",
    "                     fun_ymax=lambda y: np.mean(y)+np.std(y),#np.quantile(y,0.95), \n",
    "                     geom=\"pointrange\", position=gg.position_dodge(.02))+\n",
    "     gg.stat_summary(fun_y=np.median, geom=\"line\", position=gg.position_dodge(.02))+\n",
    " gg.theme_bw()+\n",
    " gg.ylim(0.4,.8)+gg.ylab(\"Correlation\")+gg.facet_grid(\"~lam_max\")+\n",
    " gg.theme(figure_size=(12,3))+gg.scale_x_log10()\n",
    ").draw();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- using 2 iterations generally better\n",
    "- method works for a broad range of parameter-values\n",
    "- getting `lam_sig` right is more important than `lam_max`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {

    "## Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "### influence of design on performance\n",
    "\n",
    "- manipulate experimental design parameters\n",
    "    - proportion of \"unknown\" events\n",
    "    - inter-stimulus interval (ISI)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "metadata": {

     "slide_type": "subslide"

    "colnames=np.array(res.columns)[:-4]\n",
    "df=pd.melt(res, id_vars=colnames, value_vars=[\"est_bl\",\"est_resp\",\"naive_bl\",\"naive_resp\"])\n",

   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- new method always better\n",
    "- fast-paced designs harder to estimate\n",
    "- more unmodelled events (mind-wandering?) $\\rightarrow$ worse performance\n",
    "- tonic levels more difficult to estimate than phasic response"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "## Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "### influence of misspecification\n",
    "\n",
    "- simulate data with a set of `npar`/`tmax` parameters (this is what is being manipulated)\n",
    "- recover using standard \"wrong\" pars (those are fixed, i.e., using the mean only)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 80,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"

   ],
   "source": [
    "sim_label=\"tonic_phasic2\"\n",
    "fname=os.path.join(path,\"{nb}_{sim}.ft\".format(nb=nbname,sim=sim_label))\n",
    "res=pd.read_feather(fname)\n",
    "colnames=np.array(res.columns)[:-4]\n",
    "df=pd.melt(res, id_vars=colnames, value_vars=[\"est_bl\",\"est_resp\",\"naive_bl\",\"naive_resp\"])\n",
    "df[\"tonic_phasic\"]=[\"tonic\" if \"bl\" in v else \"phasic\" for v in df.variable]\n",
    "df[\"estimate\"]=[\"new\" if \"est\" in v else \"naive\" for v in df.variable]\n",
    "(gg.ggplot(df, gg.aes(x=\"tmax_diff\", y=\"value\",color=\"estimate\"))+\n",
    "     gg.stat_summary(fun_y=np.median, \n",
    "                     fun_ymin=lambda y: np.quantile(y,0.05),\n",
    "                     fun_ymax=lambda y: np.quantile(y,0.95), geom=\"pointrange\", position=gg.position_dodge(.02))+\n",
    "     gg.stat_summary(fun_y=np.median, geom=\"line\", position=gg.position_dodge(.02))+\n",
    " gg.theme_bw()+\n",
    " gg.ylim(0,1)+gg.ylab(\"Correlation\")+gg.facet_grid(\"tonic_phasic~npar_diff\")+\n",
    " gg.theme(figure_size=(12,5))\n",
    ").draw();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- `npar` - misspecification does not matter much\n",
    "- `tmax` important to get right, both for traditional and new method\n",
    "- shorter pulses (low `tmax`) beneficial for baseline-estimation (less build-up)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "### compensate for misspecation \n",
    "\n",
    "- is it possible to compensate for `tmax`-misspecification by estimating `tmax` from data?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 85,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x450 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sim_label=\"tonic_phasic4\"\n",
    "fname=os.path.join(path,\"{nb}_{sim}.ft\".format(nb=nbname,sim=sim_label))\n",
    "res=pd.read_feather(fname)\n",
    "colnames=np.array(res.columns)[:-4]\n",
    "df=pd.melt(res, id_vars=colnames, value_vars=[\"est_bl\",\"est_resp\",\"naive_bl\",\"naive_resp\"])\n",
    "df[\"tonic_phasic\"]=[\"tonic\" if \"bl\" in v else \"phasic\" for v in df.variable]\n",
    "df[\"estimate\"]=[\"new\" if \"est\" in v else \"naive\" for v in df.variable]\n",
    "(gg.ggplot(df, gg.aes(x=\"tmax_diff\", y=\"value\",color=\"estimate\"))+\n",
    "     gg.stat_summary(fun_y=np.median, \n",
    "                     fun_ymin=lambda y: np.quantile(y,0.05),\n",
    "                     fun_ymax=lambda y: np.quantile(y,0.95), geom=\"pointrange\", position=gg.position_dodge(.02))+\n",
    "     gg.stat_summary(fun_y=np.median, geom=\"line\", position=gg.position_dodge(.02))+\n",
    " gg.theme_bw()+\n",
    " gg.ylim(0,1)+gg.ylab(\"Correlation\")+gg.facet_grid(\"tmax_fit~tonic_phasic\")+\n",
    " gg.theme(figure_size=(12,4.5))\n",
    ").draw();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- estimating `tmax` allows broader range of misspecification\n",
    "- SD for `tmax` from Hoeks & Levelt (1997) was 135 ms, so feasible range should cover most subjects"
   ]
  },
